OL,3,CPM cuts international aid to increase
OL,4,Cdefence spending to 2.5% of GDP by 2027
OL,6,FPrime Minister Keir Starmer has
OL,7,Fannounced the government will spend
OL,8,F2.5% of GDP on defence by 2027.
OL,10,FHe said he would fund the increase in
OL,11,Fspending by slashing funding for
OL,12,Foverseas aid from 0.5% of gross
OL,13,Fnational income to 0.3% by 2027.
OL,15,FIn a statement to the Commons, he
OL,16,Fsaid: "We must find courage in our
OL,17,Fhistory, courage in who we are as a
OL,18,Fnation, because courage is what our
OL,19,Fown era now demands of us.
